Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.01,0:00:05.32,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,FAMOUS DETECTIVE HOLMES
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.08,0:01:41.19,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,The Targeted Giant Coin Bank
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.47,0:01:45.49,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't feel like doing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.10,0:01:49.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Gilmore is a man who is famous\Nfor being greedy and cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.97,0:01:53.63,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, this letter doesn't\Neven explain what the case is.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.14,0:01:55.77,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's save the fun\Nuntil after we arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.91,0:01:57.71,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That appears to be our destination...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.91,0:02:00.47,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,the Valley of Gilmore.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.62,0:02:04.05,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Does he really own all of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.53,0:02:13.89,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What a dirty city this is!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.03,0:02:20.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No one looks very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.51,0:02:33.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a huge cannon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.28,0:02:34.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,A product of the Gilmore Company.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.05,0:02:37.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear he's exporting\Nthem all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.36,0:02:43.09,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.19,0:02:46.32,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.70,0:02:48.09,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.43,0:02:50.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's get out and push.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.74,0:02:58.00,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.44,0:03:01.00,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.64,0:03:03.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Push!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.41,0:03:04.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Push!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.25,0:03:09.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.05,0:03:13.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The more we push, the deeper it sinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.26,0:03:15.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.82,0:03:17.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Grab this rope!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.76,0:03:21.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody, please help!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.93,0:03:22.90,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.96,0:03:24.56,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It really is a bad road.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.67,0:03:26.13,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.50,0:03:28.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody, pull hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.00,0:03:29.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.34,0:03:31.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.08,0:03:42.05,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you really saved us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.35,0:03:44.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fortunate you guys\Nbrought extra clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.35,0:03:45.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wash these for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.59,0:03:46.95,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you stop by\Nhere on the way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.32,0:03:49.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.\NBut we didn't bring extra hats.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.69,0:03:55.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone from out of town\Nfalls in the mud.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.86,0:03:57.66,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We want to fix this road but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.80,0:04:01.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, the road is really bad,\Nthe people in this town are very nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.64,0:04:04.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, is this the road\Nto the Gilmore's mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.84,0:04:06.81,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You're visiting that mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.18,0:04:08.54,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.88,0:04:11.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then wash these yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.15,0:04:15.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry Michael.\NIt's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.39,0:04:22.91,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?\NSuddenly, everyone's...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.23,0:04:30.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Did we say something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.17,0:04:31.10,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.73,0:04:34.60,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for the Gilmore mansion,\Nit's over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.14,0:04:38.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,My goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.77,0:04:41.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that light?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.15,0:04:53.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother! Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.99,0:04:54.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.09,0:04:55.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.92,0:04:56.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.33,0:04:59.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.36,0:05:02.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He really is a great detective.\NHe's already detected us here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.60,0:05:03.89,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid! Don't admire him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.03,0:05:05.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Ignore him. Just ignore him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.24,0:05:14.80,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother, he came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.51,0:05:16.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.34,0:05:17.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this contraption for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.11,0:05:20.95,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you digging a well or something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.45,0:05:23.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.65,0:05:25.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Good cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.92,0:05:26.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't laugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.92,0:05:29.75,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Since there is so much soil,\Nit must be a very deep well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.76,0:05:33.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The water level is\Nvery low around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.46,0:05:34.12,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.20,0:05:35.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, sorry to have bothered you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.31,0:05:49.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to the mansion.\NWe have to tell the Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.86,0:06:07.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.70,0:06:09.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Loafing at work again, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.27,0:06:10.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.07,0:06:12.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Holmes! Holmes is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.03,0:06:14.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Holmes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.50,0:06:16.44,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he knows already.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.57,0:06:19.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to stop digging?\NWe've been losing to him recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.11,0:06:20.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Why you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.55,0:06:27.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,How can we stop after\Ndigging so much already!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.02,0:06:30.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop complaining and get to work!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.25,0:06:32.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes Sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.35,0:06:36.05,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,My plan is flawless!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.49,0:06:37.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Curse you Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.99,0:06:39.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is he doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.28,0:06:57.24,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.35,0:06:58.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.46,0:07:09.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.69,0:07:11.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the source of the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.66,0:07:16.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, good boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.27,0:07:22.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this gold plated?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.64,0:07:27.27,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Watson! Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.31,0:07:31.54,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.85,0:07:32.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.48,0:07:34.07,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Watson!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.15,0:07:35.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.48,0:07:36.78,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't good!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.82,0:07:38.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.75,0:07:40.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He must be the\Nsecurity for this statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.47,0:07:52.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Holmes, I presume?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.50,0:07:54.13,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You must be Mr. Gilmore.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.24,0:07:55.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks just like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.90,0:07:59.81,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I called you regarding this coin bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.01,0:08:01.91,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this statue a coin bank?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.08,0:08:04.10,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, I'll show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.77,0:08:28.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You have quite an interesting hobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.30,0:08:29.43,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.74,0:08:33.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This special coin bank is\Nthe most unique in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.41,0:08:34.24,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.34,0:08:37.14,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,on the one day of the year,\Nwhen I happily count the money...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.31,0:08:44.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,346,768... 346,769... 346...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.19,0:08:47.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no more!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.79,0:08:49.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm short of gold coins!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.92,0:08:52.86,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievably, I was\Ntwenty coins short!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.49,0:08:57.90,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But you're only twenty coins\Nshort out of 300,000 coins...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.97,0:09:00.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,346,789!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.90,0:09:07.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Since then I've done nothing\Nbut worry and I've hardly slept!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.51,0:09:10.81,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel very sorry about that.\NBut I think I'd rather go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.91,0:09:11.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.25,0:09:14.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an interesting story.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.98,0:09:17.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me give it a try.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.86,0:09:23.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.69,0:09:28.86,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He only carries gold coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.00,0:09:32.73,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He won't even take\Nfood from strangers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.67,0:09:36.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that makes me even\Nmore curious about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.67,0:09:38.47,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anybody else who\Nis friendly with this bird?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.57,0:09:40.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There's only my son, Michael.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.71,0:09:43.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I would like to talk to him.\NWould you ask him to come?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.95,0:09:47.24,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Be quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.69,0:09:56.09,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael is out right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.56,0:09:57.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He went out?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.69,0:09:59.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he wandering\Naround downtown again?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.93,0:10:04.39,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Gilmore, please understand\NMichael's feelings a little more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.73,0:10:05.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel sorry for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.80,0:10:08.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't speak so rudely to me!\NYou are merely his private tutor!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.30,0:10:11.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring him back here at once!\NThe detective wants to meet with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.14,0:10:14.11,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.68,0:10:19.27,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll talk to Michael later.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.68,0:10:21.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You can go back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.95,0:10:24.75,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that downtown over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.12,0:10:26.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I have been calling\Nthat place downtown.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.36,0:10:30.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything you can see below\Nthis mansion is all my property.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.56,0:10:33.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The town, the factory, the river,\Nthe road are all mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.20,0:10:37.63,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,And it would become\NMichael's property in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.20,0:10:39.89,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But he is really troublesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.97,0:10:41.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He always supports the poor people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.30,0:10:44.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,When did they start digging the well?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.71,0:10:46.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Two weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.51,0:10:48.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Two weeks...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.59,0:10:59.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.59,0:11:02.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He's Mr. Gilmore's son, Michael.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.57,0:11:13.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.71,0:11:20.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.74,0:11:24.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He's different from his father.\NHe's a good son.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.61,0:11:27.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think he's a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.58,0:11:28.81,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Teacher!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.05,0:11:30.95,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Jim said he has a stomach-ache.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.15,0:11:32.45,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He is not eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.99,0:11:39.39,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a little fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.49,0:11:40.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.66,0:11:42.36,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I may not look like it,\Nbut I'm a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.86,0:11:44.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a stomach-ache?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.30,0:11:45.96,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Open your mouth and say "Ahhh".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.84,0:11:49.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,A little more.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.04,0:11:54.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You should put him to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.51,0:11:55.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Come this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.61,0:11:57.44,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to give Jim a shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.55,0:12:00.41,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he has to drink bitter medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.95,0:12:02.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I don't want medicine!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.78,0:12:04.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm okay now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.15,0:12:08.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,My medicine is even\Nsweeter than honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.19,0:12:12.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Jim's lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.77,0:12:21.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Your friend really helped us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.70,0:12:25.14,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Please bring my bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.21,0:12:25.80,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.91,0:12:28.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Does Michael visit here often?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.84,0:12:32.11,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he helps me a lot.\NHe is a very sweet boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.28,0:12:35.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an honourable job, but it\Nmust be difficult to manage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.98,0:12:38.35,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's a god who forsakes us\Nand a god who saves us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.45,0:12:41.79,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But some stranger donated\Ntwenty pounds recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.22,0:12:44.75,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Twenty sovereign gold coins?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.19,0:12:48.86,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he asked, in a letter, that we\Nuse the money for this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.96,0:12:50.43,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds great.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.54,0:13:01.44,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.98,0:13:05.10,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you go on back by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.65,0:13:08.05,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I will stay for a while\Nand check on his condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.15,0:13:09.95,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Please do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.39,0:13:15.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,How is my new invention?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.39,0:13:18.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's twice as faster than before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.09,0:13:22.29,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But it makes me three\Ntimes more tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.53,0:13:24.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.30,0:13:27.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The whole fun of treasure hunting\Nis the hard work you do to get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.10,0:13:30.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Five meters till we\Nreach the gold statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.11,0:13:33.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Great! 30 cm per hour!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.64,0:13:38.87,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it suddenly got easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.38,0:13:40.35,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.25,0:13:47.31,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.26,0:13:58.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I worry too much\Njust waiting like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.17,0:14:00.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have any\Nidea about the thief?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.04,0:14:04.16,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Gilmore, what do\Nyou think of this equation?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.94,0:14:08.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,If you have to dig out soil,\Nand the height is 10 meters...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.44,0:14:10.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,and the diameter is 20 meters...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.55,0:14:14.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,how many meters do you have\Nto dig to make a tunnel...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.72,0:14:18.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,that is 3 meters high\Nand 2 meters wide?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.26,0:14:23.45,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.56,0:14:25.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that question\Nrelated to this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.63,0:14:28.36,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.67,0:14:33.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's thinner than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.14,0:14:36.47,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm paying you a lot of money!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.57,0:14:39.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll fire you if you don't find\Nthe thief by tomorrow morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.74,0:14:41.83,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps by tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.91,0:14:48.78,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do it as many times as I like.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.25,0:14:52.41,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But this is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.52,0:14:55.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that really matter?\NIt was originally their money anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.09,0:14:58.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, do you think\Nthey would be happy...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.89,0:15:01.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,if they knew you were\Ngetting the money like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.36,0:15:03.56,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But now they can buy\Nmedicine and food!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.93,0:15:06.87,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop this.\NThere is a detective here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.13,0:15:08.80,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not scared of a detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.04,0:15:10.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't stop me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.44,0:15:12.41,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,If you feel that way\Nthen tell my father!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.64,0:15:13.73,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.98,0:15:24.42,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I just can't sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.12,0:15:29.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Even at this moment, somebody must\Nbe trying to steal my gold coins!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.47,0:15:39.43,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.03,0:15:40.86,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Maria...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.97,0:15:43.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't stop me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.44,0:15:44.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.51,0:15:50.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I was the one who showed you\Ndowntown and my mother's orphanage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.11,0:15:52.31,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That is why you started doing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.08,0:15:56.24,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think you\Nwould suffer this much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.32,0:16:00.29,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I can at least help by\Nbeing a lookout for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.99,0:16:01.78,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Maria.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.90,0:16:10.80,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait here. I'll be quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.86,0:16:46.83,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say a word!\NYou burglar!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.37,0:16:50.34,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally caught you by the tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.91,0:16:52.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Go inside quietly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.04,0:16:57.77,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Come out! Lousy thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.65,0:16:59.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.45,0:17:01.41,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.65,0:17:05.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,With the help of Ms. Maria,\NI have found the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.92,0:17:06.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.22,0:17:09.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Maria, please turn on the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.89,0:17:10.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.93,0:17:18.96,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll now show you how\Nthe thief stole the gold coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.10,0:17:22.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Put birdlime on the gold coin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.34,0:17:23.36,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.18,0:17:38.65,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,A big catch!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.09,0:17:42.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,W... What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.66,0:17:43.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.99,0:17:47.29,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone can make this\Nbird carry gold coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.70,0:17:51.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You traitor bird!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.20,0:17:52.86,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,So, who's the thief?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.93,0:17:54.56,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it somebody in this house?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.70,0:17:57.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Maria, would you clean up here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.17,0:17:58.90,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.61,0:18:03.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to rush.\NPlease work quietly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.01,0:18:04.71,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.85,0:18:10.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't keep me waiting!\NJust tell me now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.62,0:18:12.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The thief is Moriarty.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.62,0:18:14.09,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Moriarty?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.22,0:18:14.78,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.92,0:18:17.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The famous Professor Moriarty.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.76,0:18:20.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,People call him the Napoleon\Nof the crime world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.60,0:18:26.36,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.53,0:18:29.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would a notorious\Nthief only steal twenty coins?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.71,0:18:35.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.11,0:18:37.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Be quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.48,0:18:40.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.98,0:18:43.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, begin now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.02,0:18:51.39,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's... it's... it's!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.39,0:18:52.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.63,0:18:53.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.60,0:18:56.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.56,0:18:58.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.54,0:19:04.87,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring it down! Bring it down!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.88,0:19:11.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,My coin bank!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.55,0:19:12.57,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.18,0:19:16.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.28,0:19:17.34,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael, come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.74,0:19:38.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.98,0:19:48.95,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.48,0:19:51.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor, there's something\Nstrange attached to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.89,0:19:53.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind!\NJust leave him like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.19,0:19:58.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.53,0:20:01.12,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael! Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.23,0:20:06.10,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up! Holmes is coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.44,0:20:15.24,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.24,0:20:16.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my son!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.58,0:20:19.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.38,0:20:20.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't cut that rope!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.48,0:20:21.28,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.15,0:20:27.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I'm scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.20,0:20:44.00,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes! What the?!\NYou can't win!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.00,0:20:45.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You! You!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.67,0:20:46.66,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.41,0:20:48.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa, let's jump!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.08,0:20:50.01,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.91,0:20:54.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Good bye Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.36,0:21:02.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Take the helm!\NThe helm!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.10,0:21:10.36,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.94,0:21:22.44,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.44,0:21:23.07,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.71,0:21:26.34,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael, you did a good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.61,0:21:29.05,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course he did. He's my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.45,0:21:32.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael is my treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.99,0:21:34.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.76,0:21:37.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,My treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.23,0:21:43.66,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,My coin bank!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.10,0:21:49.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He's hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.74,0:21:51.14,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch my gold coins!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.14,0:21:51.83,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.04,0:21:53.77,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you dirty\Nup the river like this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.87,0:21:54.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There is sludge everywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.38,0:21:58.54,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.58,0:22:06.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The important thing is\Nthat you do it on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.22,0:22:08.05,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,And never be impatient.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.29,0:22:11.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Do it on my own\Nand never be impatient.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.76,0:22:14.59,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, I think the fishing\Npole idea was ingenious.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.26,0:22:18.27,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.27,0:22:19.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Be well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.87,0:22:20.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.00,0:22:23.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye!
